## üöÄ **Quick Start**

### **Prerequisites**

- Python 3.8+
- AI Provider API Key (OpenAI, Anthropic, or others)

### **Installation**

#### **üéØ PyPI Installation (Recommended)**

```bash
# Install from PyPI
pip install rcode-cli

# Set your API key
export ANTHROPIC_API_KEY="your-api-key-here"
# or
export OPENAI_API_KEY="your-api-key-here"

# Start R-Code
rcode
```

#### **üîß Development Installation**

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/RaheesAhmed/R-Code-CLI.git
cd R-Code-CLI

# Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# Set your API key
export ANTHROPIC_API_KEY="your-api-key-here"
# or
export OPENAI_API_KEY="your-api-key-here"

# Start R-Code
python cli.py
```

### **First Run**

```bash
$ python cli.py

üöÄ Welcome to R-Code CLI v1.0.0
üß† Analyzing project structure...
üìÅ Found 42 files to analyze
‚úÖ Project analysis complete

‚îå‚îÄ R-Code Assistant
‚îÇ Hello! I'm your AI coding assistant with complete project understanding.
‚îÇ I can help you write, debug, and improve code while preventing conflicts.
‚îÇ
‚îÇ Try asking me to:
‚îÇ ‚Ä¢ "Create a new user authentication module"
‚îÇ ‚Ä¢ "Fix the bug in user_service.py"
‚îÇ ‚Ä¢ "Add error handling to the API endpoints"
‚îÇ
‚îÇ Type /help for commands or just start chatting!
‚îî‚îÄ

‚Ä∫
```

