## üí° **Usage Examples**

### **Context-Aware Development**

```
‚Ä∫ Create a new user service that follows our project patterns

üîç Using get_project_context_summary...
üìä Analyzing project structure and conventions...

I can see you're using:
‚Ä¢ Flask with SQLAlchemy ORM
‚Ä¢ Snake_case naming convention
‚Ä¢ Service-Repository pattern
‚Ä¢ JWT authentication

I'll create a user service that follows these patterns...

üìÅ Creating: src/services/user_service.py
üìÅ Creating: src/repositories/user_repository.py
üìÅ Creating: tests/test_user_service.py
```

### **Smart Validation**

```
‚Ä∫ Add a login function to auth.py

üîç Using validate_file_operation...
‚ö†Ô∏è Analysis found:
  ‚Ä¢ File auth.py already has login() function at line 23
  ‚Ä¢ Suggested: enhance existing function or create login_with_email()

üí° Should I enhance the existing login function or create a new variant?
```

### **Safe Experimentation**

```
‚Ä∫ /save "Before refactoring auth system"
‚úÖ Checkpoint saved: cp_20250208_142301

‚Ä∫ Refactor the authentication system to use JWT tokens

üîç Working on authentication refactor...
üìù Modified: src/auth/auth_service.py
üìù Modified: src/models/user.py
üìù Created: src/utils/jwt_helper.py

‚Ä∫ /undo
‚úÖ Reverted to checkpoint: cp_20250208_142301
```

